JOHANNESBURG – Troubled retailer Steinhoff has raised over R3-billion to try and boost its cash flow problems. It sold a 5,8 percent stake in Steinhoff Retail Africa to ease liquidity problems and reduce debt. Steinhoff sold 200 million shares in STAR to reduce its total shareholding to 71,1percent from 76,81percent. READ: How Steinhoff execs cooked the books The sale comes in the wake of the group’s large fall out in December in which they admitted to financial irregularities. The retailer's share price declined, wiping off over R200-billion in its market capitalisation. eNCA